  "prompt": "Which are the top 5 Bollywood songs of 2015?",
  "response": "It's tough to definitively say which songs are the \"top\" as popularity is subjective and can be measured in different ways (views, streams, awards, radio play, etc.). However, based on popularity, critical acclaim, and lasting impact, here are 5 Bollywood songs from 2015 that were highly successful and remain popular:\n\n1.  **\"Gerua\" from *Dilwale***: This song, sung by Arijit Singh and Antara Mitra, became an instant hit due to its beautiful melody, picturesque visuals, and the iconic pairing of Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol.\n\n2.  **\"Deewani Mastani\" from *Bajirao Mastani***: A visually stunning and melodically rich song, sung by Shreya Ghoshal, showcasing the grandeur of the film and Deepika Padukone's captivating performance.\n\n3.  **\"Sooraj Dooba Hai\" from *Roy***: Sung by Arijit Singh, Aditi Singh Sharma, this song had a catchy beat and became a popular party anthem and remained on charts for a long time.\n\n4.  **\"Agar Tum Saath Ho\" from *Tamasha***: A soulful and emotionally resonant song sung by Alka Yagnik and Arijit Singh, known for its poignant lyrics and Deepika Padukone and Ranbir Kapoor's acting.\n\n5.  **\"Pinga\" from *Bajirao Mastani***: Sung by Shreya Ghoshal and Vaishali Mhade, this song was appreciated for its traditional sound and the dance-off between Priyanka Chopra and Deepika Padukone.\n\nThese songs are just a selection, and many other great tracks were released in 2015. Enjoy listening!\n",
